│ "both operands are used on the LHS". That assumption is wrong for a select    │
│ pattern 'select %cmp, %cmpeq, false'. Only %cmp is always evaluated; %cmpeq   │
│ is conditionally used.                                                        │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ The bug comes from foldAndOrOfICmps (lines 3366-3373). After attempting the   │
│ fold in logical form (LHS,RHS), it retries with swapped operands but          │
│ deliberately forces IsLogical=false, converting short-circuit logical AND/OR  │
│ into bitwise AND/OR. This loses poison safety when the equality compare       │
│ (Cmp0) may produce poison but was previously guarded by the other compare in  │
│ a select. The 'samesign' attribute on an icmp is a promise; violating it      │
│ yields poison. Eliminating the guard changes semantics. The code's            │
│ justification about both operands' poison propagating is incorrect for        │
│ select-form logical ops.                                                      │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ Edit lines 3369-3373 in InstCombineAndOrXor.cpp to preserve logical semantics │
│ when the original operation was logical (IsLogical == true). Instead of       │
│ hard-coding IsLogical=false for the swapped attempt, pass through the         │
│ original IsLogical flag (or conditionally skip the second attempt when        │
